# Spring & Spring Boot - Interview Preparation (8+ Years Experience)

## 1. Spring Framework Fundamentals
- Spring Core Container (Beans, Core, Context, Expression Language)
- Spring AOP (Aspect-Oriented Programming) and Aspects
- Instrumentation
- Web (Web, Servlet, Portlet, Struts)
- Data Access/Integration (JDBC, ORM, OXM, JMS, Transactions)
- Convention over Configuration
- Microservices-ready
- Embedded servers
- Opinionated defaults

## 2. Configurations in Spring
- Understanding Dependency Injection (DI) or IoC
- XML-Based Configuration
- Annotation-Based Configuration
- Java-Based Configuration
- Spring Boot Auto-Configuration
- Externalizing Configuration (application.properties, application.yml)
- Profiles and Environment-Specific Configurations
- Overriding Default Properties
- Order of Priority of Properties in Spring

## 3. Basic Spring Boot Debugging & Fundamentals
- Understanding the Project Structure (Created by Spring Initializr)
- `src/main/java`: Application code
- `src/main/resources`: Configuration files
- `src/test/java`: Test code
- `pom.xml` or `build.gradle`: Dependency management

## 4. Core Annotations in Spring Boot
- `@SpringBootApplication`, `@Configuration`, `@ComponentScan`, `@EnableAutoConfiguration`
- `@RestController`, `@Controller`, `@Service`, `@Repository`

## 5. Spring Security
- Basic Authentication & Authorization
- Role-Based Access Control
- Implementing OAuth2 and JWT for Secure APIs

## 6. RESTful Services in Spring Boot
- Using `@RequestMapping`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`
- Handling Request & Response Bodies (`@RequestBody`, `@ResponseBody`)
- Content Negotiation & Response Status Codes (200, 201, 400, 500)
- Exception Handling in REST APIs
- Using `@ControllerAdvice` for Global Exception Handling
- Custom Exception Classes & Response Structures

## 7. GraphQL with Spring Boot
- Netflix DGS Framework & Fundamentals

## 8. Testing in Spring Boot
- Unit Testing with JUnit & Mockito
- `@SpringBootTest` & TestContainers
- BDD Testing with Cucumber

## 9. Spring Bean Scopes & Lifecycle
- Understanding Dependency Injection (DI)
- Singleton, Prototype, Request, Session, Application
- Creating Custom Beans using `@Bean` and `@Component`

## 10. Spring Boot Caching
- Introduction to Caching in Spring Boot
- Using `@Cacheable`, `@CachePut`, and `@CacheEvict`
- Configuring Cache Providers (Ehcache, Redis, Caffeine)

## 11. Asynchronous Processing in Spring Boot
- Using `@Async` for Asynchronous Methods
- CompletableFuture & Its Usage
- Configuring Thread Pools for Async Tasks

## 12. Spring Boot Actuator
- Overview & Built-in Endpoints
- Custom Actuator Endpoints
- Monitoring & Managing Applications

## 13. Spring Boot Event-Driven Architecture
- Kafka, RabbitMQ, ActiveMQ, IBM MQ

## 14. Spring Cloud Integration
- Introduction to Spring Cloud
- Configuring Spring Cloud Config Server
- Circuit Breaker Pattern with Resilience4j/Hystrix
- Distributed Tracing with Sleuth & Zipkin

## 15. Monitoring & Logging in Production
- Using ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
- Monitoring with Prometheus, Grafana, Dynatrace

## Advanced Topics

### 16. Spring Boot Performance Tuning & Optimization
- Profiling Spring Boot Applications (JVisualVM, YourKit)
- Lazy Initialization & Its Impact
- Connection Pooling (HikariCP, Tomcat JDBC)
- Caching Strategies & Cache Optimization

### 17. Spring Transactions (Advanced Concepts)
- Propagation & Isolation Levels
- Declarative vs Programmatic Transactions
- Distributed Transactions (JTA, XA)

### 18. Spring Batch Processing
- Chunk-Oriented vs Tasklet Processing
- Job Parameters & Step Execution
- Reading & Writing Data from Databases & Files

### 19. Spring Data JPA
- Connecting to databases (JDBC, JPA, Hibernate).
- **Spring Data JPA**: Advantages and usage.
- Repository pattern and CRUD operations.
- Handling transactions with `@Transactional`.
- Custom Queries using QueryDSL
- Handling N+1 Query Problem
- Fetch Joins & Projections for Optimization

### 20. Spring WebFlux (Reactive Programming)
- Understanding Reactive Streams & Project Reactor
- Flux vs Mono
- Handling Backpressure

### 21. Spring Boot Deployment Strategies
- Dockerizing Spring Boot Applications
- Kubernetes Deployment (Helm, YAML, ConfigMaps)
- Cloud-Native Considerations (AWS, Azure, GCP)

### 22. Spring Boot API Gateway & Service Mesh
- Using Spring Cloud Gateway
- Integration with Istio or Linkerd
- API Rate Limiting & Security

### 23. Advanced Spring Security
- Multi-Tenant Authentication & Authorization
- LDAP & OAuth2 Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Spring Security ACL (Access Control List)

### 24. Resilience Patterns in Spring Boot
- Bulkhead Pattern
- Rate Limiting (Using Bucket4j, Redis)
- Circuit Breakers for Microservices

### 25. Spring Boot with NoSQL Databases
- Integrating with MongoDB, Cassandra, Couchbase
- Using Spring Data MongoDB for NoSQL Queries

